cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a novel Loss-Sensitive Generative Adversarial Network (LS-GAN) and a Generalized LS-GAN (GLS-GAN) for regularized GAN models. It also extends the LS-GAN to a conditional form for supervised and semi-supervised learning problems, which are all topics related to machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the LS-GAN and GLS-GAN are used for generating new images, and the paper demonstrates their outstanding performance on image classification tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in AI research, and the LS-GAN and GLS-GAN are novel approaches to improving the performance of GANs. 

The sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as GANs are a type of neural network, and the paper presents a new approach to training GANs. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) is also possible as the paper focuses on generating new images using GANs.
